<font color="#FF0000">BLUES BROTHERS</font><br>
<tt>Mon Aug 18 10:15:47 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Dear Bill:<br><br>
Try not to lose sight of the fact that Airmen on flight status face danger routienly in peace and war.  It is inheriently dangerous to be around aircraft... on the ground or in the air.  I'm not telling you this because you are unaware of it... you KNOW what I am talking about.<br><br>
There are precious few guys like Cook Barela who engaged the enemy eyeball to eyeball and lived to tell about it.  Many of those who survived his experience are unable to articulate.  VERY few kept a written account (Notes.. diary..etc.)  Guys like Cookie are special gifts to all mankind in that they take you &quot;there.&quot;  We would have no history if it were not for those who could and did record it.<br><br>
However, his is a priviledged position.  His accounts steep with sensationalism... the kind of stuff that stirs the emotions.  The accounts of a combat Marine makes better reading than floating around at altitude in a high flying fuel dump... with nothing to worry about... except maybe a few other crews might be in a world of hurt without fuel... <br>
or there's always the possibility of a SAM flying up your ass.  Small potatoes...Right!<br><br>
Well, little brother... you need to grab both ears and pull your head out of your ass.  You may not be respected or praised by the masses.  You may be scorned by some... but the ones who really count would kiss your butt in front of Sears on a sales day.<br><br>
My brother, sitting beside me at this moment is a veteran of Hamburger Hill.  Genetically deprived of gray matter, he like Cook ended up in the infantry.  Cookie was a Marine, James served as a platoon sergeant with the 101st AB Div.  I feel like I can speak for Cook... I know that I can speak for James... and I will speak for myself, &quot;You are a man to be honored... honored by those who have honor... the rest don't count!&quot;<br><br>
Wish I could kick your butt for dragging your lip... instead I will give you an electronic hug and a hearty &quot;Welcome Home!&quot;<br><br>
Stick around... Silent Warrior and others like you and me may need you to &quot;refuel US&quot; when we fall on our own swords.<br><br>
God Bless You... Birdman!<br><br>
Mustang Two Four
